  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nCurrently the syncing simulator waits for a particular epoch before ending. I think this mimics the beacon simulator. \r\n\r\nI think the faster and more accurate test should be that a node achieves sync. The test should end once all connected nodes are in sync, rather than waiting for some pre-determined epoch. \r\n\r\nThis will also help with dissecting the logs, as sync logs will be closer to the end of the test. There should of-course be a timeout which fails the test if nodes don't reach sync.\r\n",
